{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/06-02-building-trust-by-giving-trust","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"date: 2015-06-02T22:41:58-05:00"}],"topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"title":"Building Trust by Giving Trust","color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"},"platforms":[{"name":"Brunow","introducedAt":"2017.01.20"}]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2015"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One of the quickest ways you can erode my trust is by asking me to sign something at the wrong time. Like an NDA before you discuss a project with me or a contract in a situation where a friendly handshake would do."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"My policy is when in doubt, trust. You trusting me will make me trust you more. A positive cycle."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/06-02-building-trust-by-giving-trust"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/brunow","title":"Brunow","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he.","type":"text"}],"role":"collection"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/Archive":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/archive","title":"Archive","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"All posts","type"